From: Nick Hawkins <nick.hawkins@hpe.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] media: add GXP thumbnail video capture driver

Add a V4L2 video capture driver for the HPE GXP SoC thumbnail video
engine. The engine captures low-resolution frames of the host video
output for remote KVM sessions.

The driver exposes a standard V4L2 capture device at /dev/video0.
The hardware operates at 32 bits per pixel (XRGB8888) reported as
V4L2_PIX_FMT_XRGB32, or 16 bits per pixel reported as V4L2_PIX_FMT_RGB24.

Key design decisions:
- DMA-direct capture into VB2 buffers (eliminates intermediate memcpy)
- Frame rate enforcement via ktime-based throttling
- Per-device state instead of global variables
- Proper spinlock irqsave/irqrestore pairing
- Bounds checking on DV timings with buffer size recalculation

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Nick Hawkins <nick.hawkins@hpe.com>
